[UART-PAR-001] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement the four compile-time parameters defined in Table 3-2 with the VHDL names G_CLK_FREQ_HZ, G_DEFAULT_BAUD, G_FIFO_DEPTH, and G_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT, and the equivalent SystemVerilog names P_CLK_FREQ_HZ, P_DEFAULT_BAUD, P_FIFO_DEPTH, and P_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT, with the specified types, defaults, and valid ranges.
  verification: inspection
  [GENERATED]

[UART-PAR-002] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement the FIFO depth parameter (G_FIFO_DEPTH in VHDL, P_FIFO_DEPTH in SystemVerilog) as a power of 2 in the range 8 to 256 inclusive.
  verification: analysis
  [GENERATED]

[UART-PAR-003] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall produce an elaboration-time assertion failure with a descriptive message identifying the parameter name and violated constraint when any compile-time parameter is instantiated with a value outside its specified range. In VHDL the assertion severity shall be failure. In SystemVerilog $fatal shall be used.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-PAR-004] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall accept a system clock frequency parameter (G_CLK_FREQ_HZ / P_CLK_FREQ_HZ) in the range 1,000,000 to 1,000,000,000 inclusive specifying the system clock frequency in Hz.
  verification: analysis
  [GENERATED]

[UART-PAR-005] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall accept a default baud rate parameter (G_DEFAULT_BAUD / P_DEFAULT_BAUD) in the range 1 to CLK_FREQ_HZ / 2 inclusive specifying the target baud rate at reset.
  verification: analysis
  [GENERATED]

[UART-PAR-006] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall accept a timeout default parameter (G_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT / P_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT) in the range 0 to 65535 inclusive specifying the TIMEOUT_VAL register reset value in baud clock ticks. A value of 0 disables the receive timeout at reset.
  verification: analysis
  [GENERATED]

[UART-PAR-007] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall compute the BAUD_TUNING register reset value (C_BAUD_TUNING_RESET in VHDL, LP_BAUD_TUNING_RESET in SystemVerilog) as round(DEFAULT_BAUD × 2³² / CLK_FREQ_HZ) using round-to-nearest arithmetic. Truncation shall not be used for this computation.
  verification: analysis
  [GENERATED]

[UART-PAR-008] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall set the FIFO_CTRL register reset value (C_FIFO_THRESH_RESET in VHDL, LP_FIFO_THRESH_RESET in SystemVerilog) such that TX_THRESH and RX_THRESH each equal FIFO_DEPTH / 2, providing threshold interrupts at half-full by default.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-PAR-009] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall size the FIFO_STATUS TX_LEVEL and RX_LEVEL fields as 8-bit unsigned integers capable of representing occupancy values 0 to FIFO_DEPTH inclusive for all supported values of FIFO_DEPTH.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-IF-001] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement an AXI-Lite slave interface compliant with the ARM AMBA AXI4-Lite specification.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-IF-002] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall provide an AXI-Lite data width of 32 bits.
  verification: inspection
  [GENERATED]

[UART-IF-003] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall provide an AXI-Lite address width sufficient to address all defined register offsets within the peripheral address space.
  verification: inspection
  [GENERATED]

[UART-IF-004] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall accept single-beat AXI-Lite read and write transactions only. Burst transactions shall not be supported.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-IF-005] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall accept AWVALID and WVALID arriving in any order on the write address and write data channels, and shall not complete the write transaction until both have been accepted.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-IF-006] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall return OKAY (2'b00) on BRESP for all successful write transactions.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-IF-007] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall return OKAY (2'b00) on RRESP for all successful read transactions.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-IF-008] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall return SLVERR (2'b10) on BRESP for write transactions to undefined address offsets.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-IF-009] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall return SLVERR (2'b10) on RRESP for read transactions to undefined address offsets.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-IF-010] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall silently ignore writes to read-only registers or reserved fields. Register content shall be unchanged following such a write.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-IF-011] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall allow AXI-Lite read and write transactions to different registers to proceed without interference.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-IF-012] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall provide a single-ended TX output and RX input conforming to standard UART signal conventions: idle high, active-low start bit.
  verification: inspection
  [GENERATED]

[UART-IF-013] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall support 8-bit data frames.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-IF-014] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall support a start bit of one bit duration preceding each data field.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-EN-001] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall treat UART_EN as the master enable. When UART_EN is deasserted all UART transmit and receive activity shall cease and both TX and RX paths shall be held inactive.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-EN-002] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall enable the transmit path independently via TX_EN. Deasserting TX_EN shall not affect RX path operation provided UART_EN remains asserted.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-EN-003] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall enable the receive path independently via RX_EN. Deasserting RX_EN shall not affect TX path operation provided UART_EN remains asserted.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-EN-004] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall give TX_EN and RX_EN no effect when UART_EN is deasserted.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-EN-005] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall connect the TX data path to the RX data path internally when LOOP_EN is asserted, driving the TX output normally while ignoring the external RX pin.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-EN-006] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall apply LOOP_EN only while UART_EN is asserted.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-BR-001] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement a 32-bit NCO accumulator for baud rate generation. On every system clock cycle the value in BAUD_TUNING shall be added to the accumulator and the carry-out shall generate one baud clock pulse.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-BR-002] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall produce a baud rate equal to (BAUD_TUNING × F_clk) / 2³² where F_clk is the system clock frequency.
  verification: analysis
  [GENERATED]

[UART-BR-003] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall reset BAUD_TUNING to C_BAUD_TUNING_RESET = round(G_DEFAULT_BAUD × 2³² / G_CLK_FREQ_HZ). At default values of G_DEFAULT_BAUD = 115,200 and G_CLK_FREQ_HZ = 100,000,000 this yields 0x004FA6D5 with error less than 0.0001%.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-BR-004] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall silently ignore writes to BAUD_TUNING while UART_EN is asserted, leaving the accumulator tuning word unchanged.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-BR-005] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall disable baud clock generation when BAUD_TUNING = 0x00000000. No baud clock pulses shall be produced and no UART framing activity shall occur.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-BR-006] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall produce the minimum supported baud rate without undefined behavior when BAUD_TUNING = 0x00000001.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FF-001] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall support 8 data bits per frame.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FF-002] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall append one stop bit per transmitted frame when STOP_BITS = 0.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FF-003] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall append two stop bits per transmitted frame when STOP_BITS = 1.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FF-004] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall accept frames with one stop bit on receive regardless of the STOP_BITS setting.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FF-005] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall transmit and accept frames with no parity bit when PARITY = 2'b00.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FF-006] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall generate and verify odd parity on every frame when PARITY = 2'b01. A parity mismatch shall set PARITY_ERR in STATUS and INT_STATUS.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FF-007] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall generate and verify even parity on every frame when PARITY = 2'b10. A parity mismatch shall set PARITY_ERR in STATUS and INT_STATUS.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FF-008] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assert the parity bit in every transmitted frame when PARITY = 2'b11 (mark parity). On receive, a mark parity bit of logic 0 shall set PARITY_ERR in STATUS and INT_STATUS, as this indicates a line error or sender misconfiguration. This check is retained as a diagnostic in noise-sensitive environments where silent corruption is unacceptable.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FF-009] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall set PARITY_ERR in STATUS when a parity error is detected by the receiver. This flag shall remain set until the STATUS register is read.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FIFO-001] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement separate TX and RX FIFOs each with a depth of G_FIFO_DEPTH entries of 8 bits.
  verification: inspection
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FIFO-002] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assert TX_FULL in STATUS when TX FIFO occupancy equals G_FIFO_DEPTH, and deassert it when occupancy falls below G_FIFO_DEPTH.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FIFO-003] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assert TX_EMPTY in STATUS when TX FIFO occupancy equals zero, and deassert it when the first byte is written to the TX FIFO.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FIFO-004] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assert RX_FULL in STATUS when RX FIFO occupancy equals G_FIFO_DEPTH, and deassert it when occupancy falls below G_FIFO_DEPTH.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FIFO-005] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assert RX_EMPTY in STATUS when RX FIFO occupancy equals zero, and deassert it when the first received byte is transferred to the RX FIFO.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FIFO-006] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall silently ignore a write to TX_DATA while TX_FULL is asserted. The TX FIFO content shall be unchanged.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FIFO-007] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall discard the incoming byte when an RX overrun occurs (a received frame completes while the RX FIFO is full), preserving all existing RX FIFO content unchanged.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FIFO-008] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall reflect the current TX FIFO occupancy as an 8-bit unsigned integer in FIFO_STATUS.TX_LEVEL, readable at any time regardless of UART_EN state.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-FIFO-009] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall reflect the current RX FIFO occupancy as an 8-bit unsigned integer in FIFO_STATUS.RX_LEVEL, readable at any time regardless of UART_EN state.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-TO-001] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall disable the receive timeout mechanism entirely when TIMEOUT_VAL = 0x0000. No timeout event shall occur regardless of RX FIFO state.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-TO-002] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall start the timeout counter when the RX FIFO transitions from empty to non-empty, provided TIMEOUT_VAL is non-zero.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-TO-003] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall restart the timeout counter on each subsequently received character while the RX FIFO remains non-empty.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-TO-004] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall hold the timeout counter inactive and prevent timeout expiry when the RX FIFO is empty.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-TO-005] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall set TIMEOUT_FLAG in STATUS when the timeout counter reaches TIMEOUT_VAL without a new character being received.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-TO-006] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall keep TIMEOUT_FLAG set until the RX FIFO is read to empty.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-TO-007] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall set the TIMEOUT bit in INT_STATUS when timeout expiry occurs, provided INT_ENABLE.TIMEOUT_EN is asserted at the time of expiry.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-INT-001] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall provide eight interrupt sources: TIMEOUT, TX_THRESH, RX_THRESH, TX_EMPTY, RX_FULL, PARITY_ERR, FRAME_ERR, and OVERRUN.
  verification: inspection
  [GENERATED]

[UART-INT-002] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement sticky INT_STATUS bits. Once set by a hardware event each bit shall remain set until software writes 1 to the corresponding INT_CLEAR bit.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-INT-003] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall retain INT_STATUS bits when the underlying hardware condition clears. INT_STATUS bits shall not self-clear.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-INT-004] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall produce no effect on INT_STATUS when 0 is written to any INT_CLEAR bit.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-INT-005] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall return zero on all reads of INT_CLEAR.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-INT-006] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall reset INT_ENABLE to 0x00, masking all interrupt sources at power-on.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-INT-007] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assert the top-level IRQ output when any INT_STATUS bit is set and its corresponding INT_ENABLE bit is asserted.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-INT-008] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall deassert the IRQ output when no INT_STATUS bit has a corresponding asserted INT_ENABLE bit.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-INT-009] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall set TX_THRESH in INT_STATUS when TX FIFO occupancy falls strictly below FIFO_CTRL.TX_THRESH.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-INT-010] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall set RX_THRESH in INT_STATUS when RX FIFO occupancy rises strictly above FIFO_CTRL.RX_THRESH.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-INT-011] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall set OVERRUN in INT_STATUS on each RX overrun event when INT_ENABLE.OVERRUN_EN is asserted.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-INT-012] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall set PARITY_ERR in INT_STATUS on each parity error detection event when INT_ENABLE.PARITY_ERR_EN is asserted.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-INT-013] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall set FRAME_ERR in INT_STATUS when a framing error is detected — specifically when the stop bit field does not contain a valid stop bit — when INT_ENABLE.FRAME_ERR_EN is asserted.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-001] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall locate all registers at 32-bit aligned offsets within the peripheral address space.
  verification: inspection
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-002] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall return zero from all reserved fields on any read.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-003] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall silently ignore writes to reserved fields, leaving reserved field content unchanged.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-004] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall return all registers to their defined reset values following assertion of the peripheral reset input.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-005] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign CTRL[7] as the UART_EN master enable bit per UART-EN-001.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-006] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign CTRL[6] as the TX_EN transmit enable bit per UART-EN-002.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-007] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign CTRL[5] as the RX_EN receive enable bit per UART-EN-003.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-008] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign CTRL[4] as the LOOP_EN loopback enable bit per UART-EN-005.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-009] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign CTRL[3:2] as the PARITY field per UART-FF-005 through UART-FF-008.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-010] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign CTRL[1] as the STOP_BITS field per UART-FF-002 and UART-FF-003.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-011] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall reserve CTRL[0] as read-only zero.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-012] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement STATUS as a read-only register, silently ignoring writes.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-013] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall reset STATUS to 0x00000300 reflecting TX_EMPTY=1 and RX_EMPTY=1 at power-on with all error flags deasserted.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-014] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign STATUS[11] as TIMEOUT_FLAG per UART-TO-005.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-015] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign STATUS[10] as INT_PENDING, reflecting the current state of the IRQ output.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-016] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign STATUS[9] as TX_FULL per UART-FIFO-002.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-017] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign STATUS[8] as TX_EMPTY per UART-FIFO-003.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-018] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign STATUS[7] as RX_FULL per UART-FIFO-004.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-019] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign STATUS[6] as RX_EMPTY per UART-FIFO-005.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-020] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign STATUS[5] as TX_BUSY, asserted while the transmit shift register is actively shifting a frame.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-021] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign STATUS[4] as RX_BUSY, asserted while the receive shift register is actively receiving a frame.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-022] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign STATUS[3] as PARITY_ERR per UART-FF-009.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-023] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign STATUS[2] as FRAME_ERR, asserted when a framing error is detected per UART-INT-013.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-024] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign STATUS[1] as OVERRUN, asserted when an RX overrun occurs per UART-FIFO-007.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-025] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall reserve STATUS[0] as read-only zero.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-026] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign BAUD_TUNING[31:0] as the NCO tuning word per UART-BR-001 through UART-BR-006.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-027] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement BAUD_TUNING as a read-write register, returning the current tuning word on any read regardless of UART_EN state.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-028] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall silently ignore writes to BAUD_TUNING while UART_EN is asserted per UART-BR-004.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-029] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign FIFO_CTRL[15:8] as TX_THRESH, the 8-bit TX FIFO interrupt threshold per UART-INT-009.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-030] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign FIFO_CTRL[7:0] as RX_THRESH, the 8-bit RX FIFO interrupt threshold per UART-INT-010.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-031] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall reset FIFO_CTRL such that TX_THRESH = RX_THRESH = G_FIFO_DEPTH / 2 per UART-PAR-008.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-032] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement FIFO_STATUS as a read-only register.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-033] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign FIFO_STATUS[15:8] as TX_LEVEL per UART-FIFO-008.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-034] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign FIFO_STATUS[7:0] as RX_LEVEL per UART-FIFO-009.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-035] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign TIMEOUT_VAL[15:0] as the receive timeout count in baud clock ticks per UART-TO-001 through UART-TO-007.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-036] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall reset TIMEOUT_VAL to G_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-037] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign INT_ENABLE[7:0] as individual enable bits for each interrupt source per UART-INT-006. Bit positions shall correspond to INT_STATUS bit positions.
  verification: test
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-038] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement INT_STATUS as a read-only register, silently ignoring writes.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-039] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement INT_STATUS bits as sticky per UART-INT-002 and UART-INT-003.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-040] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall assign INT_STATUS bit positions as: [7] TIMEOUT, [6] TX_THRESH, [5] RX_THRESH, [4] TX_EMPTY, [3] RX_FULL, [2] PARITY_ERR, [1] FRAME_ERR, [0] OVERRUN.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-041] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement INT_CLEAR with W1C behavior per UART-INT-002 and UART-INT-004.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-042] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall return zero from INT_CLEAR on all reads per UART-INT-005.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-043] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall align INT_CLEAR bit positions with INT_STATUS bit positions.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-044] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement SCRATCH[31:0] as a read-write register with no hardware function.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-045] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall retain any written 32-bit value in SCRATCH and return it unchanged on all subsequent reads until overwritten.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-046] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall reset SCRATCH to 0x00000000.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-047] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall enqueue a transmitted data byte in the TX FIFO when TX_DATA[7:0] is written.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-048] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall silently ignore a write to TX_DATA while TX_FULL is asserted per UART-FIFO-006.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-049] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement TX_DATA as a write-only register, returning 0x00000000 on reads.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-050] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall return the oldest byte in the RX FIFO and dequeue it when RX_DATA is read.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-051] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall treat the value returned by RX_DATA as undefined when RX_EMPTY is asserted. Software shall verify RX_EMPTY is deasserted before reading RX_DATA.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-REG-052] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement RX_DATA as a read-only register, silently ignoring writes.
  verification: (pending review)
  [GENERATED]

[UART-RST-001] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall implement a synchronous active-high reset input.
  verification: inspection
  [GENERATED]

[UART-RST-002] The Buffered AXI-Lite UART shall return all registers to their defined reset values on assertion of reset as specified in Section 8.
